article.headline: East Carolina 77, Hampton 53
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Derrick Wiley scored 15 points to lead East Carolina to a 77-53 win over Hampton on Tuesday night. Wiley made 6 of 12 attempts from the field and 3-of-4 from the free throw line. Erroyl Bing added 13 points and Belton Rivers and Gabriel Mikulas each posted 11 for the Pirates (6-1). Bing and Mikulas also grabbed eight rebounds apiece. East Carolina held Hampton (3-8) to 35 percent shooting from the field and turned 27 Hampton turnovers into 32 points. East Carolina shot 48 percent from the field and made 38.5 percent from 3-point range. The Pirates shot 66.7 percent from the free throw line. Frank Russell was the only Hampton player to score in double figures, pitching in 17 points.
